@NODE Install "How to install ..."


	First: This tool was made to protect Harddisks, but if you dont
	       trust us you may try to protect a Floppydisk or even your
 	       RAD: first, only to see how it works.


 1. Run the Installer to copy all the needed files to your SYS: Volume  

 2. Open a Shell and type:

	"Enigmainit <Drive:> <Password> ENCRYPT"

    Example:

	 "Enigmainit RAD: Irule ENCRYPT"

	(This may take a little time !)
	The Password is - offcourse - casesensitive 
	Keep it well in your mind !

 3. Type "dir <Drive:>"  (Just for info) 

 4. Cancel the "No Dos Disk in Drive ...." Requester

 5. Type "EnigmaII rmd <Drive:>"

	- this "rmd" is the first CLI-Parameter, important to run the patch
 
 6. Enter your Password 

 7. Type "Dir <Drive:>"

 8. Enjoy it

  Now the Crypter for the specified Drive is installed. 

  If you want to make your Drive a non-Dos Volume again Reset your Amiga 
  or type "EnigmaII rmd <Drive:>


  If you have Encrypted your HD, simply add the line

	"EnigmaII rmd <Drive:>" 
  
  	in your startup-sequence before you assign anything 
  	to the Crypted Partition !
  
 		Remember not to Crypt your Boot-Partition ! 

	See also @{"New Features" LINK NewSecure} for additional informations


@ENDNODE

@NODE Remove "How to remove ..."

 1. Make sure that the Patch is removed !
    
    ( Type: "EnigmaII rmd <Drive:>" ) and promt the "Patch removed" Requester

 2. Type:

	"Enigmainit <Drive:> <Password>"

	DO NOT MISSPELL THE PASSWORD !!!  

 3. Be patient.

 4. The Drive is decrypted now.



 Shit, i have misspelled my Password, what can I do ?

	Type:

	"Enigmainit <Drive:> <MisspelledPW> ENCRYPT"
	"Enigmainit <Drive:> <CorrectPW>"

	... now you have an decrypted Device.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Require "System Requirements"




	What we expect is Kickstart 2.0, Reqtools 

	and a little System-knowledge

	What we recommend is a Harddisk, more than 1 Mb RAM
       
        and an accelerated Amiga.




@ENDNODE
@NODE Work "How does it work?"

	The ENIGMAII Project protects your Harddisks against access 
	of unauthorized Persons.

	Therefore all Data on your Drive will be modified. While
	installing this tool we will Crypt your Drive with the specified
	Password using a very complex and safe algorithm.

	After this you need to install a patch, which allows you to
	access the Drive properly. The Patch prompts you for a 
	Password (casesensitive!), Enter the correct one and access 
	the Drive.

	If you Enter a wrong Password, the patch uses this PW to decrypt
	your Drive, an you will get the "No Dos Disk in Drive ..." Requester.
	No Problem ... remove the Patch and install it again for a second try.

	Due to security we do not check, if the Password is correct.
@ENDNODE
@NODE Safe "How Safe is it ?"



	... very safe 

	You can type a Password with up to 16 chars (more will ignored).

	The Crypt/Decrypt Table and Routine will generated depending on

	your PW. It is Save, even if you know the Original contens of a 

	special Block.

	Maybe someone tries out all possible Passwords to get access....

	He tries only 60 of the Possible 256 chars and needs 
	
	i. e. 1/10 sec to see that he was wrong:

	16 chars/PW and 60 possible chars:

	60^16 = 2.821109907*10^28 * 1/10 sec

	= 8.945680833*10^21 years (worst case) 


		... We (personally) think, that this is enough


	
	Every CLI or Workbench launched Program will work fine with 

	this Patch. Including DiskSalv, Quarterback and so one.

	This is a very System-Friendly patch made for Multitasking-

	Environments.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Speed "How Fast is it ?"


	This tool was tested on several Amigas:

	On my (Hosot) A1200 with 6Mb Ram and a 250 Mb Conner AT-Bus HD
	the HD-Speed (according to Sysinfo) is 480 kB with the
	Patch installed and 480 kB without the Patch. 
	Only the CPU is more Busy while Reading/Writing Data.

	On Harvesters A2000 with 68020/14 Mhz ,no 32-Bit Ram
	and a 210 Mb Quantum and a SupraWordSyncII-Controller
        the Speed is 250 kB with the Patch installed
	and 700 kB without the Patch.

	On Rages A4000/40 the HD Speed decreases from 1.6 Mb to 1.4 Mb
	due to the Patch.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Question "What is if ..."

	... I want to run my BBS with this Patch, and I only want 
	to enter the Password if I switch my Computer on to allow
	my Mother to Reset the BBS if fucked up and I am not at home ...

  
	You can type "EnigmaII <drive:> <Password>" to access a drive.
	
	If you do this, no Requesters will appear. Simply Mount a RAD:
	at Power-On, copy a startup-sequence containing the line above
	to this RAD: and boot from it.
	Assign all the System-Dirs back to your DH0: and do something
	like "execute DH0:s/startup-sequence". Use the Tool A-Lock
	in addition, to protect your computer completely.


	
	... My HD is seriously damaged due to System-Crash while 
	Writing to it.

	First try to fix your Problems using i.e. Disksalv.
	If this wont work (this case is most unlikely) you can 
	Decrypt your HD and try it again. See @{"How to remove" LINK Remove}
	I have no idea why it should work then, I only want to
	say: no matter, how many Blocks have Bad Checksums or so,
	you are always able to Decrypt the Drive (You will get the 
	same Bad Checksums of course, but the Drive is decrypted and 
	you can't blame us). 
	 
	

	... I want to change my Password

	First you have to @{"Decrypt" LINK Remove} your Drive.
	Then you can Crypt it again. See @{"How to Install" LINK Install} 

@ENDNODE
@NODE Error "The Fatal one"

	If you Powerdown your Amiga or a Guru-Meditation appears 
	while En/DeCrypting a Drive (not while running the patch!)
	your Data will be damaged seriously !!!!

	So do not touch your Computer or the Fuses while Installing/
	Removing this Tool.

		... no other Bugs are known
	
@ENDNODE
